LAGOS – The new Managing Director of the Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN), Capt. Rabiu Yadudu has charged staff of the agency to embrace discipline in their day-to-day activities. Yadudu also said that FAAN as a leading agency in the country’s aviation industry should improve itself in adoption of technologies, saying that the industry was moving towards hi-tech. A statement by Mrs. Henrietta Yakubu, the General Manager, Corporate Communication, FAAN stated that Yadudu made the comments yesterday in Abuja when he officially received the reins of office from his predecessor, Engr. Saleh Dunoma who stepped down on Monday after five years of service. The statement hinted that the agency was going to concentrate on improving itself in all ramifications, stressing that to do this, there must be consistent discipline among staff. He said: “Primarily, I need to say in the next few months, we are going to concentrate on improving ourselves and I think the best way we are going to improve the agency is to discipline ourselves. We must sustain a high level of discipline year-in-year-out as it allow you to perform to the best of your ability. “Secondly, respect. We must maintain a high standard of personal discipline in the discharge of our professional responsibilities, with these qualities, we can accomplish all.” Yadudu insisted that without key qualities of respect and discipline, the agency would not attain increased professionalism and growth. He also commended his predecessor, Dunoma for instilling professionalism in the agency, describing him as a thorough leader whose wealth of experience could still be tapped into.